WEBVTT

00:00:00.500 --> 00:00:04.000
Hello, welcome to basic dog training.

00:00:04.500 --> 00:00:09.000
Today we'll learn how to effectively teach the "sit" command.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:15.000
The foundation of dog training is consistency and positive reinforcement.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:22.000
First, hold a treat in your hand to get your dog's attention.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Move the treat slowly above their nose, which will naturally make them sit.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:33.000
The moment they sit, say "sit" and immediately give the treat.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Repeating this process several times a day in short sessions is most effective.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:45.000
Be patient during training and celebrate your dog's successes.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Next time, we'll learn about the "stay" command.